Admission for school

Admission for primary and secondary school

The basic requirements for admission to the German School New Delhi are a good command over the German language and availability of seats in the respective group/class.  In case sufficient seats are not available in the individual groups/classes then a waiting list will be drawn up for admission.
Please read more information:

    Primary school 1-4/ Schulisches Angebot
    Secondary school I - 5-10/ Schulisches Angebot
    Secondary school II - 11 - 12/ Schulisches Angebot

Application formalities

For applying to the DSND, please fill up both the forms and send them together with two and three copies of the passport and reports respectively to the school’s administration office by email to the following email address: sekretariat@dsnd.de

Interactive session

On completion of the above formalities, we will hold an interactive session with you at a previously agreed upon date.  In order to enable you to get to know the School better and for us to get to know you better, we will fill up a questionnaire together with you during the course of our discussions and after taking inputs from you.

Needless to say, all the information furnished by you will be kept confidential. If you wish, a representative of the school’s parents’ council would be glad to guide you through the process as well.

The DSND is a recognised overseas German school which imparts education to its pupils in keeping with the aims and objectives of the German education system and leading up to German school leaving qualifications. Apart from this, the School also strives to acquaint its pupils with Indian culture, nurture interpersonal and cultural ties through extra-curricular activities and foster mutual understanding. In the backdrop of this objective, the school also welcomes pupils of nationalities other than German if they have a good command over the German language, seats are available in the school and this does not violate the legal and regulatory environment of the host country in any manner.

All decisions relating to admission to the kindergarten or school shall be taken jointly by the principal of the School and one board member of the German School Association New Delhi.

We thank you for your interest in the DSND and your willingness to co-operate with us.

School Management
German School Association New Delhi
Parents’ Council of the German School New Delhi
